<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4689111>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 18. — Arcoscalpellum michelottianum (Seguenza, 1876), PROSPEC, stn CPH 10; A-B, peduncle of two specimens; C, right lateral view; note the change in peduncular plate patterns from the smaller specimen A to the larger one C. Abbreviations: cl, carinolateral scale; l, lateral scale; rl, rostro-lateral scale; sc, subcarinal scale; sr, subrostrum scale. Scale bars: 5 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4689111/files/figure.png" .

